author: Brianne Tolj
title: Sydney rain causes homes to collapse in Marrickville | Daily Mail Online
text: Homes collapse and residents evacuated after a month's worth of rain lashes Sydney in an HOUR Heavy rain and thunderstorm have lashed Sydney on Tuesday, with more wild weather expected on the way Residents at a Marrickville apartment building in Sydney's inner-west evacuated amid fears it would collapse Up to 100 people were evacuated from an apartment building in the inner-west suburb of Marrickville The block of units was under threat of collapsing following a landslide at the back of the complex Several trees and a large chunk of soil fell into an old brick pit after heavy rain and severe thunderstorm Published: 03:11 GMT, 7 February 2017 | Updated: 11:03 GMT, 7 February 2017 329 shares
